@database C2X
@FONT COURIER.FONT 13
@INDEX "index.guide/main"
@NODE Main "C2X"
@TOC "rexx.guide/Built-In FUNCTION LIBRARY INDEX"
@{b}C2X()@{ub}

Usage:@{b}C2X(string)@{ub}

Converts the string argument from its character representation to the
corresponding hexadecimal number, expressed as the ASCII characters 0-9 and A-F.

See also: @{"C2B()" LINK "C2B/main"}

Example:
@{fg shine}
        say c2x('abc')                  ==>616263
@{fg text}
@ENDNODE
